<font color="#FF0000">WHAT'S GOING ON?</font><br>
<tt>Thu Sep  4 21:52:11 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
P.S.  Based on the wars between Doc Spatz and the other folks that post here.  I just want to say this.  Right or wrong I feel that I am ready to go off on somebody.  I don't know if it is from Cook's stories that bring up old memories but no resolutions;  I don't know if it is the communication between Silent Warrior and Ed, making me feel if I am reading a private conversation...I don't know if it is Doc Spatz's responses or Cook's vehemence.  But somebody is going to call me on something and I feel like I'm going to unload on them.<br><br>
The conversations that were had here involved issues that as vets we have to deal with on a daily basis.  Pain was expressed and feelings were worked through.  Issues that were based in the past but that had to be dealt with today.<br><br>
Right or wrong I feel that this not happening now.  Do we need to get back to that or has the site a different purpose now?  I worked long and hard to get where I am today and my issues around Vietnam.  This site provided an outlet for vets all over the country to post.  The efforts of Doc Spatz and others should not be belittled.  It was a joint effort for all involved.  In fact, for your information, this site was originally put toghether by Marc Weiss.  A war protestor.  Stange, huh?<br><br>
So, boys and girls, this is my rant.  Mine alone.  Is there a renewal of focus required or like Doc Spatz has said &quot;the Barbarians are at the gate?&quot;              <br><br>
Most of the folks who posted here with any regularity are gone.  Reasons vary, but mostly the comments were lack of caring and healing.  The comments about vets sharing problems and as a group helping, supporting and welcoming other home  is no longer here.  All who post have issues here and all work through them differently.  So what's up?
<p><code>-- cbotkins@visuallink.com  (Chet Botkins) </code><p>


